  "texts": [
    "We fine-tune the models on the different splits outlined in Section 5.",
    "We keep the hyperparameters and compute budget constant (which were tuned on the validation sets of the 'Uniform' splits), which we outline in Appendix D. Training occurs at the article level, using publisher-level labels.",
    "We binarize the article publisher's MBFC label for training labels: all 'Questionable Source', 'Conspiracy-Pseudoscience', and 'Satire' publishers were deemed unreliable -, and all others reliable +.",
    "Other publisher-label mappings have been used in other works, and is deserving of future research for this dataset.",
    "To assess model performance at the article level, we employ the F1-score computed independently for each class along, with the Matthews Correlation Coefficient (MCC)."
  ],
